docs {
  ## Get Headers

  Retrieves block headers matching given query. By default it will fetch current head slot blocks.

  ### Query Parameters
  - `slot` (optional) - Fetch headers for the given slot.
  - `parent_root` (optional) - Fetch headers filtered by parent root (hex encoded with 0x prefix).

  ### Response (200)
  ```json
  {
    "execution_optimistic": false,
    "finalized": true,
    "data": [
      {
        "root": "0xcf8e0d4e9587369b2301d0790347320302cc0943d5a1884560367e8208d920f2",
        "canonical": true,
        "header": {
          "message": {
            "slot": "1",
            "proposer_index": "1",
            "parent_root": "0x4b363db94e286120d76eb905340fcd4e979ae41e26b22f72b66852b3e8e3377b",
            "state_root": "0x7e76880eb67bbdc86250aa578958e9d0675e64e714337855204fb5abaaf82c2b",
            "body_root": "0xa18c58fbe20e8e1271e5c8a30842e007e9e89f4ede60b88c8c18ffafc3eb3b20"
          },
          "signature": "0x1b66ac1fb663c9bc59509846d6ec05345bd908eda73e670af888da41af171505cc411d61252fb6cb3fa0017b679f8bb2305b26a285fa2737f175668d0dff91cc1b66ac1fb663c9bc59509846d6ec05345bd908eda73e670af888da41af171505"
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  ```
}
